The Bruthen Blues festival committee regrets to announce the cancellation of the 2020 Bruthen Blues and Arts Festival. 
Due to the current and continuing bushfire situation and the heavy toll it is taking on our community, our committee, our volunteers and the larger community, we have regrettably come to the decision to cancel this years festival. 
Anybody who has purchased tickets/booked a market stall, will be refunded shortly. We apologise for any inconvenience or upset this may cause to any of our valued festival goers and encourage you all to still plan a trip to Bruthen (and the greater East Gippsland area) once the fire situation has eased.

Robin Johnson
Well-known local musician Robin Johnson has been a regular at the Blues Festival Jam for many years now and this year she will be performing on the Saturday Street Stage with a band formed especially for the festival. The band features Drew Cassidy on guitar, Ben Curnow on bass, David Long on drums, Niq Reefman on trumpet, and Eva Grunden on backing vocals. They will be performing their versions of a variety of blues.
